Description: Typical range for industrial Nd:YAG laser cleaning systems; starting at 100W balances efficiency and safety for Ti's high reflectivity and melting point (~1668°C). Max avoids substrate damage via thermal accumulation. Source: IPG Photonics specs and studies on Ti alloy cleaning (e.g., J. Laser Appl. 2018).
